{"key":"processedPost-16980629","value":{"id":16980629,"first":16979581,"last":16990523,"when":1349579978,"utime":"10/07/12 06:19 AM","cleanedPost":"You want the least amount of flow possible to give a clean work area.&nbsp; Work right up against the face of the filter.&nbsp; If you have too much flow, it stirs up turbulence and knocks contaminants off your hands, clothes, etc., and they can swirl around and end up in your sterile work.&nbsp; Also, since no filter is 100% efficient, some contaminants are going to get through.&nbsp; If you're running a high flow rate there is a corresponding increase in contaminant load to the work area.<br />RR"}}